HERBARIUM

FLORIDA STATE UNIVERSITY

Galax urceolata (Poir.) Brummitt
(Galax aphylla L. is synonym)
This is an update of the species name to make it consistent with Flora of the 
Southern and Mid-Atlantic States (Working Draft of 30 November 12) by 
Alan S. Weakley. It is not meant to reflect verification of the previous 
identification.
Austin Mast and Michelle Smith
May 21, 2015

Distribution of the
A. C. MOORE HERBARIUM (USCH)
University of South Carolina - Columbia

FLORA OF SOUTH CAROLINA
PICKENS COUNTY

Galax aphylla Linnaeus
Diapensiaceae
This is a glabrous 
herb. Flowers in a raceme on a 
nonbracteate scape. Has 5 
white petals. Stamens united 
into a corona-like tube. Found 
at Table Rock State park, 
located on S.C. 11 west of I-
26. It was at the top of the 
mountain on the north side 
facing Table Rock lake, in a 
wooded damp area.

D. Cothran 12                    7 Oct. 1995

Handwritten text: D. Cothran 12 and 7 Oct. 1995

*Galax urceolata*
*Galax aphylla*
